Wash and dry all produce (except green beans). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Drain @pineapple{4%oz} over a #small bowl{}, reserving juice. Stir @cherry jam{2%tbsp}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tbsp}, half the @white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, 1/4 tsp @ancho chili powder{1/4%tsp} (be sure to measure; you'll use more later), and @sugar{2%tsp} into bowl with reserved pineapple juice.

> For 4 servings, use all the vinegar, 1/2 tsp chili powder, and 3 tsp sugar.

Melt 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add pineapple and scallion whites. Cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4), @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @ancho chili powder{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings; we sent more). Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Pierce @green beans{6%oz} bag with a #fork{}; place bag on a plate. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: No microwave? No problem! Steam beans in a small pot with a splash of water until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

Carefully transfer beans to a #medium bowl{} and toss with 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Pour in jam mixture. Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened and glossy, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: It's ready when it coats the back of a spoon.

Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Add chicken to pan and turn to coat in sauce. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}, then divide between plates along with chicken and green beans. Drizzle chicken with any remaining sauce. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.